24/07/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The chief secretary of the Bulgarian Interior Ministry, Boyko Borisov, said Saturday (23 July) that the police have broken an international human trafficking channel. Police arrested 17 foreigners and five Bulgarians involved in the criminal network, Borisov said, specifying that the foreigners were Moldovan citizens. The group was involved in trafficking people with fake documents from Moldova, via Bulgaria, to Greece and Italy. (bTV, BNR - 23/07/05)
